(firstQuint)Vitamin Deficiencies and Suppletion in Morbid Obesity.

 Vitamin B12 deficiency accounts up to 23-64% bariatric surgery.

 The investigators purpose is to evaluate the most effective treatment for vitamin B12 deficiency in patients who underwent a Roux-en-Y gastric bypass.

 Daily oral use of vitamin B12 tablets are may be as effective as vitamin B12 injections.

